.TH POOL_VAULT 8 "2025" "POOL Protocol" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
pool_vault \- POOL encrypted file vault
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pool_vault
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pool_vault
provides encrypted file storage and transfer over the POOL protocol.
Files are chunked, encrypted with the session key, and transferred
using POOL channel 1.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B push \fIfile peer_ip\fR
Encrypt and transfer a file to the specified POOL peer.
.TP
.B pull \fIfile peer_ip\fR
Retrieve and decrypt a file from the specified POOL peer.
.TP
.B serve \fIdirectory\fR
Serve files from the specified directory to incoming POOL requests.
.TP
.B status
Show vault daemon status and recent transfer history.
.SH PROTOCOL
Vault uses POOL channel 1 for all file transfers. Files are split into
chunks matching the session MTU, encrypted end-to-end, and reassembled
on the receiver using POOL's fragment reassembly mechanism.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/pool/vault/
Default vault storage directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR poolctl (8),
.BR pool_relay (8)
